The paper deals with the modeling and analysis of device-to-device (D2D) communications in cellular networks, which involves signal-to-noise and interference ratio (SINR) analysis in fading channels. This topic falls under the broad area of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes an optimization framework for coexisting D2D and cellular communications, which involves power control and access control, and considers coverage probability and area spectral efficiency (ASE) as performance metrics. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the areas of control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and game theory (cs.GT).
